Hell yeah, you do.
O'Connell works!

10:13.197 --> 10:16.200
Looks great too.
His smile is almost wider than his face.

10:16.200 --> 10:19.119
JERRY: <i>Twenty combat
and survival experts plus one alien</i>

10:19.119 --> 10:21.288
<i>will hunt each other
in our warehouse complex</i>

10:21.288 --> 10:23.332
<i>filled with weapons and booby traps.</i>

10:23.332 --> 10:25.459
<i>Every three hours,
the playing field shrinks,</i>

10:25.459 --> 10:27.377
<i>last man standing wins.</i>

10:27.377 --> 10:29.546
- Sounds good. Wish me luck.
- You got this.

10:29.546 --> 10:30.464
Kick ass, buddy.

10:30.464 --> 10:32.174
See you in six hours or so.

10:32.174 --> 10:33.050
[alarm blares]

10:33.050 --> 10:34.343
[gunfire and explosions]

10:34.343 --> 10:36.720
That should occupy Yumyulack
for the rest of his birth-a-day.

10:36.720 --> 10:38.138
You know,
despite the fact he's hosting

10:38.138 --> 10:40.390
a deadly Hunger Squid Game
Battle Royale,

10:40.390 --> 10:42.309
O'Connell seems like a great guy.

10:42.309 --> 10:44.144
You guys, I freaking won!

10:44.144 --> 10:45.479
That was a blast.

10:45.479 --> 10:46.522
Some of those guys were tough.

10:46.522 --> 10:47.856
So, what are we doing now?

10:47.856 --> 10:48.941
KORVO/JESSE:
Uh--

10:48.941 --> 10:50.359
[alarm blaring]
AUTOMATED VOICE: <i>Danger,</i>

10:50.359 --> 10:53.195
<i>radiation level at 60 percent.</i>

10:53.195 --> 10:54.321
[alarm blaring]

10:54.321 --> 10:56.114
[volptar growling]

10:56.114 --> 10:57.574
[footsteps thudding]

10:57.574 --> 10:58.742
AISHA:
<i>That's the volptar!</i>

10:58.742 --> 10:59.993
<i>Run, Pupa!</i>

10:59.993 --> 11:01.203
[volptar roars]

11:01.203 --> 11:01.995
[Pupa yells]

11:03.288 --> 11:04.289
AISHA:
<i>Watch out for the pit.</i>

11:04.289 --> 11:05.916
<i>That shit's got no bottom.</i>

11:05.916 --> 11:07.793
<i>That's where I throw used batteries.</i>

11:08.126 --> 11:09.545
<i>I know what you're thinkin',</i>

11:09.545 --> 11:13.173
<i>you wanna use those flares
to propel your ass down the pit.</i>

11:13.173 --> 11:15.717
<i>What the? Where did you get
that Rocketeer mask?</i>

11:15.717 --> 11:18.428
<i>You better not have bought that
with my Discover card.</i>

11:18.428 --> 11:20.097
<i>Pupa, no!</i>

11:20.097 --> 11:23.642
♪ heroic music ♪

11:23.642 --> 11:31.066
♪

11:31.066 --> 11:32.401
[woman screaming]

11:32.776 --> 11:35.404
<i>Guten tag,</i> tiny creature!

11:35.946 --> 11:37.614
<i>Danke</i> for the hug!

11:40.033 --> 11:40.868
[woman grunts]

11:40.868 --> 11:43.829
Ah, it feels so strange not to be falling.

11:43.829 --> 11:46.331
I've been in that pit
for two whole <i>wochen.</i>

11:46.331 --> 11:48.083
AISHA: <i>How the hell did you get
in there, German lady?</i>

11:48.083 --> 11:50.335
I Airbnb-ed a room on this spaceship.

11:50.878 --> 11:52.838
AISHA: <i>Now, now, now hold it
right there, Pupa.</i>

11:52.838 --> 11:54.506
<i>I know you wanna use
your last rope</i>

11:54.506 --> 11:56.175
<i>to send the socks
and sandals lady back</i>

11:56.175 --> 11:58.302
<i>so you can keep looking
for the UPS man, but--</i>

11:58.302 --> 11:59.136
[winch rattles]

11:59.136 --> 12:01.763
<i>That's right, I stuck
a wrench in your winch,</i>

12:01.763 --> 12:04.433
<i>so you can't save
this lady's life until I say so.</i>

12:04.433 --> 12:06.810
<i>Either you clip yourself in too
and come back with her</i>

12:06.810 --> 12:09.146
<i>or you both die of radiation,
up to you.</i>

12:09.146 --> 12:10.522
Please, don't let me die.

12:10.522 --> 12:13.400
Not before I've seen
the Straits of Mackinac.

12:14.902 --> 12:17.279
AISHA: <i>Thank you.
How hard was that?</i>

12:17.779 --> 12:19.823
[woman screams]

12:20.324 --> 12:22.326
AISHA: <i>Sorry, Pupa.
I know you wanted to--</i>

12:22.910 --> 12:24.536
<i>Son of a bitch!</i>

12:24.536 --> 12:26.413
AUTOMATED VOICE:
<i>Extreme danger,</i>

12:26.413 --> 12:29.124
<i>radiation level at 80 percent.</i>

12:29.833 --> 12:31.668
Okay, we got one more thing planned.

12:31.668 --> 12:34.505
Just keep that bucket hat down.
A little further.

12:34.505 --> 12:36.798
And... now!

12:37.799 --> 12:40.052
[gasps]
The Hat On A Hat Hat Factory?

12:40.052 --> 12:42.554
No way. They're my favorite
North American hat brand.

12:42.554 --> 12:44.806
- How'd you know?
- We looked at your search history.

12:44.806 --> 12:47.059
It was all hats, cats, and felching picks.

12:47.059 --> 12:51.104
Come on, let's go.
We got you the four-hour VIP tour.

12:54.900 --> 12:56.777
JESSE: Oh.
YUMYULACK: Holy shit,

12:56.777 --> 12:58.403
that's Barry Hatfield.

12:58.403 --> 13:01.073
He's the designing mastermind
behind all their best headwear!

13:01.073 --> 13:03.033
Mastermind, please,
this guy's a clown.

13:03.033 --> 13:04.576
He's clearly about to do
some kind of Willy Wonka--

13:04.576 --> 13:05.869
[clown horn beeps]

13:05.869 --> 13:08.455
Oh, wow, your legs do work!

13:08.956 --> 13:09.915
Indeed.

13:09.915 --> 13:11.667
Greetings and welcome

13:11.667 --> 13:14.419
to the Hat On A Hat
Hat Factory VIP Tour.

13:14.419 --> 13:17.130
'Tis I, Barry Hatfield.

13:17.130 --> 13:19.091
Shall we begin?

13:19.091 --> 13:20.717
Fuck yes.

13:21.009 --> 13:23.804
<i>♪ Come on, let's go ♪</i>

13:24.346 --> 13:26.265
<i>♪ And I'll show you hats ♪</i>

13:26.265 --> 13:28.976
<i>♪ Of different shapes and sizes ♪</i>

13:29.726 --> 13:32.104
<i>♪ Stetsons, fedoras ♪</i>

13:32.104 --> 13:33.647
<i>♪ Sailor caps ♪</i>

13:33.647 --> 13:37.609
<i>♪ And Gatsbys too ♪</i>

13:37.609 --> 13:38.777
This song sucks shit.

13:38.777 --> 13:39.945
Let it go, man.

13:39.945 --> 13:41.154
Let it go.

13:41.154 --> 13:44.116
<i>♪ We melt down felt
and press it into hats ♪</i>

13:44.116 --> 13:47.327
<i>♪ In a process
that meets EPA standards ♪</i>

13:47.327 --> 13:50.664
<i>♪ We just reopened
our porkpie wing ♪</i>

13:50.664 --> 13:56.086
<i>♪ And it's asbestos-free ♪</i>

13:56.545 --> 13:58.755
Oh, oh, yeah!

13:58.755 --> 14:00.841
Yumyulack, would you like
to learn the secret

14:00.841 --> 14:03.468
to how we make our everlasting flat brims?

14:03.468 --> 14:05.679
[gasps] That's one of
the most tightly kept secrets

14:05.679 --> 14:07.389
in all of the haberdashdom!

14:07.389 --> 14:09.808
Oof, that was some
real candy-ass bullshit.

14:09.808 --> 14:11.810
That song did just kinda peter out.

14:11.810 --> 14:14.104
I cannot wait to bust
Yumyulack's balls about it.

14:14.104 --> 14:15.981
If you thought I was bad before,
wait until tomorrow.

14:15.981 --> 14:18.025
Mm, I can almost taste the pot roast.

14:18.025 --> 14:19.693
Actually, we were kind of hoping

14:19.693 --> 14:22.362
to keep the pause going
on the whole ball-busting thing

14:22.362 --> 14:24.448
even after Yumyulack's birth-a-day.

14:24.448 --> 14:25.282
What?

14:25.282 --> 14:28.410
Today's my birth-a-day,
and you hid it from me?

14:28.410 --> 14:30.621
- Oh, shit.
- Oh, Yum, I'm so sorry.

14:30.621 --> 14:31.580
How could you?

14:31.580 --> 14:34.958
I was gonna use my birth-a-day powers
to do so much cool stuff.

14:34.958 --> 14:37.753
Oh, yeah? Because we were scared
you were gonna be violent with it.

14:37.753 --> 14:39.796
I was just gonna use my powers
to make them show me

14:39.796 --> 14:41.840
an early cut of <i>Solo 2: Solo-er.</i>

14:41.840 --> 14:44.635
Oh, and I was gonna kill everyone,
starting with you two!

14:44.635 --> 14:46.011
TERRY/JESSE: Ah!
KORVO: Oh! No!

14:46.011 --> 14:47.930
- Ah, the felt!
- Oh no!

14:47.930 --> 14:49.598
- It's burning!
- We knew you were bad!

14:49.598 --> 14:51.350
Oh, oh, Terry, Jesse, no!
[Terry/Jesse shouting indistinctly]

14:51.350 --> 14:52.601
BOTH:
Ah!

14:52.601 --> 14:55.562
♪ intense music ♪

14:55.562 --> 14:58.398
[machinery clanking, hissing]

14:58.398 --> 14:59.358
[bell dings]

14:59.358 --> 15:01.485
My family got milned into hats

15:01.485 --> 15:04.112
just like the fortune cookie
said they would!

15:07.533 --> 15:10.160
Oh, my God.
Terry, Jesse, can you hear me?

15:10.160 --> 15:12.621
You fuck.
You turned them into the lamest thing!

15:12.621 --> 15:14.248
When I open my birth-a-day present,

15:14.248 --> 15:15.666
you're gonna wish
you were a hat.

15:15.666 --> 15:20.796
♪ dramatic music ♪

15:21.713 --> 15:23.131
[car tires screech]
[cars honking]

15:23.590 --> 15:26.343
[cars honking]

15:26.718 --> 15:28.178
[car honks]
KORVO: Hold on.

15:28.178 --> 15:29.972
This chase sequence looks familiar.

15:29.972 --> 15:32.099
Are these cheap bastards reusing animation

15:32.099 --> 15:34.017
from when Jesse chased
you home that one time?

15:34.017 --> 15:35.686
No way, this is different!

15:36.520 --> 15:37.896
[dog barks, growls]

15:37.896 --> 15:39.439
Ah! Ah! Oh God.

15:39.439 --> 15:41.275
Oh, oh, help me.
Ah, ah!

15:41.275 --> 15:42.234
Oh!

15:45.988 --> 15:49.116
It is the same, th-th-that's the dog
that bit you before.

15:49.116 --> 15:50.993
Don't you dare use it to get past me.

15:50.993 --> 15:52.536
Fuck you,
that's exactly what I'm doing.

15:52.536 --> 15:54.746
[alarm blaring]

15:54.746 --> 15:56.790
AISHA:
<i>Pupa, get out of my engine room...</i>

15:56.790 --> 15:58.375
<i>you know it's not safe... here.</i>

15:58.709 --> 16:01.628
AUTOMATED VOICE:
<i>Radiation building, 98 percent.</i>

16:01.628 --> 16:02.504
[UPS Guy whimpers]

16:02.504 --> 16:04.464
Help! Please help!

16:04.464 --> 16:07.009
AISHA [voice glitching]:
<i>No, Pupa, you're not gonna make it.</i>

16:07.009 --> 16:09.678
♪ heroic music ♪

16:09.678 --> 16:11.763
Who are you?
What are you?

16:12.639 --> 16:13.849
[bone cracks]
Ah!

16:14.391 --> 16:15.726
[alarm continues blaring]

16:15.726 --> 16:18.520
♪ suspenseful music ♪

16:18.520 --> 16:20.105
- AUTOMATED VOICE: <i>99.6 percent.</i>
- Let it go, man.

16:20.105 --> 16:21.773
Yeah, I'll get fired, but fuck 'em.

16:21.773 --> 16:23.442
They make me pee in my truck!

16:23.442 --> 16:27.738
AUTOMATED VOICE: <i>Warning,
radiation buildup is now at 99.8 percent.</i>

16:28.197 --> 16:30.574
<i>Emitters are spooling,
purge imminent.</i>

16:30.574 --> 16:33.160
♪ dramatic music ♪

16:33.869 --> 16:36.371
Volptar!
[volptar screeches]

16:36.371 --> 16:38.081
AISHA:
<i>Pupa, watch out!</i>

16:38.081 --> 16:39.583
AUTOMATED VOICE:
<i>Warning, danger,</i>

16:39.583 --> 16:41.543
<i>initiating teleron wipe.</i>

16:41.543 --> 16:43.754
[volptar screeches]

16:44.338 --> 16:45.881
[explosion booms]

16:46.757 --> 16:47.925
Korvo?

16:47.925 --> 16:49.510
Korvo! [grunts]

16:51.094 --> 16:52.221
Get out of my way.

16:52.221 --> 16:54.389
Look, I understand
y-you're about to wreck me

16:54.389 --> 16:55.432
with your birth-a-day powers,

16:55.432 --> 16:58.727
but before you do that,
I just wanna say I'm sorry.

16:59.978 --> 17:01.688
You are? For what?

17:01.688 --> 17:03.023
We shouldn't have lied to you.

17:03.023 --> 17:04.942
We should have trusted you
to do the right thing

17:04.942 --> 17:06.193
instead of thinking the worst.

17:06.193 --> 17:07.069
Yeah, that's right.

17:07.069 --> 17:09.071
And I'm sorry I busted
your balls so hard.

17:09.071 --> 17:12.157
The truth is, I have thin skin.

17:12.157 --> 17:14.284
Literally, it's a clinical condition
I was born with

17:14.284 --> 17:15.327
that I've hidden from everyone.

17:15.327 --> 17:16.995
It makes me lash out
when I feel attacked.

17:16.995 --> 17:18.956
Thanks for opening up
to me about it.

17:18.956 --> 17:21.166
I had no idea you were
carrying that burden.

17:21.166 --> 17:22.417
I know it's just you and me now

17:22.417 --> 17:24.795
because you killed half the family
by turning them into hats.

17:24.795 --> 17:27.464
But I'd love to turn a new page
in how we treat each other.

17:27.464 --> 17:28.173
What do you say?

17:28.173 --> 17:29.216
You know what, Korvo?

17:29.216 --> 17:30.801
If you really mean what you just said,

17:30.801 --> 17:33.720
then okay, I'm good with letting
my birth-a-day clock run down.

17:33.720 --> 17:35.097
Really, you are?

17:35.097 --> 17:37.391
Yeah, wanna go watch
<i>Hunt for Red October 2:</i>

17:37.391 --> 17:38.517
<i>The Search for Green November?</i>

17:39.518 --> 17:41.436
Wait a hot fucking second.

17:41.895 --> 17:43.772
You hate that movie,
and the Yumyulack I know

17:43.772 --> 17:45.065
would never cave that quick.

17:45.065 --> 17:46.775
Wait, don't, that's my present!

17:46.775 --> 17:48.402
"To Korvo"?

17:48.402 --> 17:51.572
Oh, my God,
it's my Shlorpian birth-a-day.

17:51.572 --> 17:53.407
You guys pretended
to distract Yumyulack

17:53.407 --> 17:56.076
while the whole time
you were actually distracting me!

17:56.076 --> 17:58.579
Wait a minute, googly eyes?

17:58.579 --> 18:00.873
Are these hats even Terry and Jesse?

18:00.873 --> 18:02.583
[radio signal beeping, hissing]

18:02.583 --> 18:03.917
We're blown, we're blown!

18:03.917 --> 18:05.627
To the panic room!

18:06.378 --> 18:09.506
[evil laughter]

18:09.506 --> 18:11.049
Don't do this, Korvo.

18:11.049 --> 18:13.260
Think back to what you said
two seconds ago.

18:13.260 --> 18:15.679
Fuck you,
completely different situation.

18:15.679 --> 18:18.473
When I hit full bars,
your asses are grasses.

18:18.807 --> 18:20.976
Oh, ah! Whoa!

18:22.227 --> 18:23.228
Get in here!

18:24.646 --> 18:26.273
Why did you lead him back to the house?

18:26.273 --> 18:28.483
YUMYULACK: I'm sorry,
I got way too into character.

18:28.483 --> 18:31.403
♪ dramatic music ♪

18:31.403 --> 18:32.446
Oh, shit.

18:33.780 --> 18:35.032
[lock clicking]

18:36.575 --> 18:37.659
Phew.

18:37.659 --> 18:39.703
KORVO:
All charged up, time to die!

18:40.287 --> 18:42.122
[monitor crackling]

18:42.873 --> 18:45.834
That creature perished
to save <i>mein</i> life.

18:45.834 --> 18:48.003
I will get a tattoo of him on my back.

18:48.003 --> 18:49.546
I don't even know his name.

18:49.546 --> 18:52.591
AISHA: <i>He was the Pupa,
and he was very important,</i>

18:52.591 --> 18:55.260
<i>which is why the three of us
need to get our story straight</i>

18:55.260 --> 18:56.720
<i>about what exactly happened to him.</i>

18:57.721 --> 19:00.307
[volptar roars]
[all scream]

19:00.307 --> 19:02.100
[volptar roars]

19:05.103 --> 19:07.898
AISHA:
<i>Pupa, you're alive, how?</i>

19:08.774 --> 19:12.069
<i>You hid from the radiation
inside the volptar!</i>

19:12.069 --> 19:14.196
Alright, well, I'm gonna go.

19:14.696 --> 19:16.323
I don't trust this computer at all.

19:16.323 --> 19:19.952
Me neither, I've had quite enough
of this sci-fi <i>scheisse.</i>

19:21.787 --> 19:22.913
Ya know, it's funny.

19:22.913 --> 19:25.374
I've always asked,
"What can Brown do for you?"

19:25.374 --> 19:28.585
But this is the first time
somebody did something for Brown.

19:30.003 --> 19:31.129
AISHA:
<i>Wow, Pupa.</i>

19:31.129 --> 19:32.923
<i>You really taught me something today,</i>

19:32.923 --> 19:34.758
<i>that every human life matters,</i>

19:34.758 --> 19:38.804
<i>even that lonely UPS guy
was worth sacrificing your own--</i>

19:38.804 --> 19:39.888
Ponies!

19:39.888 --> 19:42.766
AISHA: <i>I knew it,
you need to quit putting toys on my card.</i>

19:42.766 --> 19:44.518
<i>You gonna fuck up my credit.</i>

19:44.518 --> 19:48.272
[Korvo laughing maniacally]

19:48.272 --> 19:50.232
KORVO: Last door.
You guys are fucked.

19:50.232 --> 19:52.109
I suppose it was always
gonna end like this.

19:52.109 --> 19:53.652
We had a good run, Terry.

19:53.652 --> 19:55.612
I just wish that
the moon had hit my eye

19:55.612 --> 19:58.448
like a big pizza pie just-a-once-a.

19:58.448 --> 20:01.326
At least I found
this bucket hat before I died.

20:01.326 --> 20:04.121
♪ dramatic music ♪

20:04.121 --> 20:04.913
[metal clinks]

20:06.290 --> 20:08.125
Prepare to meet your makers,
you lying--

20:08.125 --> 20:10.836
DEEP VOICE:
<i>Shlorpian birth-a-day complete.</i>

20:10.836 --> 20:13.422
[machine whirs]

20:15.340 --> 20:16.383
It's fine, you guys.

20:16.383 --> 20:18.343
- You can come over.
- You aren't still mad?

20:18.343 --> 20:19.636
Just at myself.

20:19.636 --> 20:21.180
I told you the lesson
I needed to hear,

20:21.180 --> 20:22.472
and then I immediately didn't do it.

20:22.472 --> 20:24.725
I was like, "Fuck that lesson,
I'm gonna slaughter you all."

20:24.725 --> 20:25.559
I-I'm sorry.

20:25.559 --> 20:29.479
Infinite power is intoxicating,
I always said that.

20:29.479 --> 20:31.148
Or wait, was it "Characters Welcome"?

20:31.148 --> 20:32.357
I know I said one of 'em.

20:32.357 --> 20:35.235
Either way, the next time
someone has Shlorpian birth-a-day,

20:35.235 --> 20:37.279
we need to trust
they won't kill the rest of us.

20:37.279 --> 20:38.030
Can we do that?

20:38.030 --> 20:40.157
- You bet.
- Absolutely.

20:40.157 --> 20:42.159
♪

20:44.077 --> 20:45.245
Oh, fuck.

20:45.746 --> 20:46.538
Yeah.

20:46.538 --> 20:47.956
- Whoa! Crazy.
- Alright, nice.

20:47.956 --> 20:50.125
I feel like I'm actually
on Air Force One.

20:50.125 --> 20:51.335
Where'd you get this game?

20:51.335 --> 20:52.336
The Reagan Library.

20:52.336 --> 20:54.463
Now, now remember,
keep those goggles on good and tight

20:54.463 --> 20:55.506
for maximum VR.

20:58.342 --> 20:59.593
Jesse's a total snake.

20:59.593 --> 21:01.261
If she gets her hands on this,
we're dead.

21:01.261 --> 21:02.763
Then I say we stuff it
in the washing machine.

21:02.763 --> 21:03.972
It's the last place she's gonna look.

21:03.972 --> 21:05.015
She only has one outfit.

21:05.015 --> 21:06.433
Whoa, look at that!

21:06.433 --> 21:07.935
Nancy's giving some guy a hummer,

21:07.935 --> 21:09.978
and it's Clint Eastwood?

21:09.978 --> 21:11.480
[gasps] Too real.

21:11.480 --> 21:13.023
[gags] I'm gonna puke.

21:13.023 --> 21:15.692
Oh, no, wait. You have to see
how she spits it in his face.

21:16.276 --> 21:18.987
[gasps] You motherfuckers.

21:18.987 --> 21:20.781
- Give me that box!
- Run!

21:20.781 --> 21:22.115
JESSE:
Give me that right now.

21:22.115 --> 21:23.951
I have a lot of anger to work out!

21:23.951 --> 21:25.494
